Installation:

git clone <GIT-ADDRESS> ~/.vim

Create relative symlinks:

ln -s .vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
ln -s .vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc


Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

cd ~/.vim
git submodule init
git submodule update


To add a module, first run (in ~/.vim):

git submodule add git://github.com/<USER>/vim-<MODULE>.git bundle/<MODULE>
git submodule init
git submodule update

Then edit .gitmodules and add a new line:

	ignore = untracked

to the end of the block describing the new submodule.  See the existing
modules in .gitmodules for an example.

This allows 'git submodule update' to update those modules even though
their directories may contain help-tag files generated by
running pathogen#helptags().
